
// This Hyperlambda code sends a socket signal to a specific session, transmitting a message of type "system". The message is constructed using the [strings.concat] slot, which concatenates strings to form the message content. The signal is sent to the session specified in the [.arguments] node.
sockets.signal:x:@.arguments/*/session
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:system
